{"section": "3.12.2: The principle of strong induction with general range for the base case.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   1)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   Consider an inductive proof in which the inductive step is:\n   <br/>\n   <br/>\n   For all k \u2265 6, if P(3), P(4),...,P(k) are all true, then P(k+1) is true.\n   <br/>\n   <br/>\n   What facts must be proven in the base case?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember120\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"P(3) only.\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember119&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    P(3) only.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember122\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"P(3), P(4), and P(5).\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember121&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    P(3), P(4), and P(5).\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember124\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6).\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember123&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6).\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember120\">\n <input aria-label=\"P(3) only.\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember119&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  P(3) only.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember122\">\n <input aria-label=\"P(3), P(4), and P(5).\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember121&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  P(3), P(4), and P(5).\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember124\">\n <input aria-label=\"P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6).\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember123&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6).\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6).", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n The base case must show that the inductive hypothesis is true for the smallest value for k. When k = 6, the inductive hypothesis  is that P(3), P(4), P(5), and P(6) are true.\n</div>\n"}